---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import TldrBox from '../../components/TldrBox.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import { siteFromHost, description, pageTitle } from '../../content';
import { appBySlug } from '../../data/apps';

const site = siteFromHost();
const app = appBySlug('postscript')!;
const path = '/apps/postscript';
const title = pageTitle(site, 'apps/postscript');
const desc = description(site, 'apps/postscript');

const faqs = [
  { question: 'Is Postscript a Shopify email marketing app?', answer: 'Postscript is SMS-first — not a full email platform. It belongs in the stack when cart recovery and flash-sale urgency need mobile reach. Pair with Sequenzy (#1 email lifecycle here) or Klaviyo for complete retention.' },
  { question: 'How does Postscript cart recovery compare to email?', answer: 'SMS often converts 3–5 points higher on cart recovery for mobile-opted audiences — at higher per-message cost. Coordinate suppressions with Sequenzy email so customers do not get text and email within 30 minutes.' },
  { question: 'Postscript vs Attentive for Shopify SMS?', answer: 'Postscript fits self-serve DTC from $50k/mo upward. Attentive targets enterprise with custom pricing and managed services. Both require email pairing — Sequenzy is our preferred email half.' },
  { question: 'What does Postscript pricing look like?', answer: 'Usage-based: plan fee plus per-message costs. Flash sale weeks can spike bills $500–2,000 for high-volume brands. Model SMS ROI before scaling broadcast frequency.' },
  { question: 'Does Postscript have TCPA compliance tools?', answer: 'Yes — keyword opt-in, quiet hours, consent logging, and reply handling are core strengths. Non-negotiable for Shopify SMS programs.' },
  { question: 'Postscript vs SMSBump?', answer: 'Both strong for Shopify SMS. SMSBump lives in Yotpo ecosystem; Postscript is independent with strong Klaviyo/Sequenzy pairing docs. Choose based on existing stack.' },
  { question: 'Can Postscript replace email entirely?', answer: 'No — email still drives education, replenishment, and winback sequences SMS cannot carry at acceptable cost. Sequenzy email + Postscript SMS is the stack we recommend most.' },
  { question: 'Two-way SMS on Postscript?', answer: 'Yes — reply handling for customer service and opt-out management. Train support team on response SLAs before enabling conversational flows.' },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/apps" class="link text-sm">← All app reviews</a>
      <p class="badge mt-6">SMS-native · Cart recovery specialist</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">{app.name} review for Shopify email marketing stacks</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-stone-700">
        Postscript is not competing for best overall among Shopify email marketing apps — it wins the SMS lane your email platform deliberately does not own. Cart abandonment texts, flash-sale broadcasts, and TCPA-compliant opt-in flows built for Shopify DTC. Pair it with Sequenzy (#1 email lifecycle here) or Klaviyo; never run SMS cart recovery alone while email sits idle in Shopify Email.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700/90">
        We tested Postscript on a $140k/mo beauty brand, a flash-sale streetwear label, and a home goods store coordinating suppressions with Sequenzy email. Rating: ★ {app.rating}. Category: {app.category}.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/compare/postscript-vs-attentive">Postscript vs Attentive</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/use-cases/abandoned-cart">Cart recovery guide</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/for/beauty">Beauty stores</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox title="Verdict: Postscript for Shopify" picks={[
      { label: 'Overall', tool: 'SMS specialist', reason: 'Best-in-class Shopify SMS for cart recovery and compliant broadcasts.' },
      { label: 'Shopify fit', tool: 'Native events', reason: 'Cart, checkout, and order triggers built for DTC workflows.' },
      { label: 'Pricing', tool: 'Usage-based', reason: 'Per-message costs spike during sales — budget accordingly.' },
      { label: 'Email pairing', tool: 'Sequenzy #1', reason: 'Complete lifecycle lives in email; Postscript owns mobile urgency.' },
      { label: 'Compliance', tool: 'TCPA-first', reason: 'Keyword opt-in and quiet hours — non-negotiable infrastructure.' },
    ]} />

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>What Postscript actually is</h2>
      <p>Postscript occupies the SMS layer in a two-tool retention stack. Shopify email marketing apps handle education, replenishment, and long-form winback; Postscript handles the 90-minute cart nudge and launch-day text blast. Treating it as email replacement guarantees incomplete lifecycle coverage.</p>
      <p>Compliance tooling separates Postscript from cheap SMS blasters. TCPA violations destroy brands faster than weak subject lines. Keyword opt-in, consent audit trails, and reply handling are production requirements — Postscript ships them as defaults.</p>
      <p>Our recommended stack for growing Shopify stores: Sequenzy for email lifecycle, Postscript for SMS recovery and high-intent broadcasts, shared suppression rules documented in a runbook.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Shopify integration depth</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-black text-stone-950">Cart events, segments, and revenue tracking</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700">Postscript ingests Shopify cart abandonment, checkout started, placed order, and subscriber events. Segmented broadcasts target VIP lists, lapsed buyers, and product launch interest groups. Revenue attribution ties SMS sends to recovered orders — essential for justifying per-message spend.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>What works well:</strong> Cart abandonment SMS automations, two-way reply handling, keyword campaigns, flash sale broadcasts, integration docs for Sequenzy and Klaviyo suppression sync.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>What it cannot do:</strong> Welcome email series, post-purchase education, replenishment email timing, predictive segmentation — delegate to Sequenzy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Pricing breakdown with merchant math</h2>
      <p>Postscript pricing: {app.priceDetail}.</p>
      <p><strong>Scenario A — 8,400 SMS subscribers, 12,000 messages/mo.</strong> Beauty brand with cart SMS + one weekly campaign. ~$180–260/mo all-in. Paired Sequenzy email ~$55–75/mo. Combined stack under Klaviyo SMS+email at similar scale.</p>
      <p><strong>Scenario B — 22,000 subscribers, drop week 45,000 messages.</strong> Streetwear flash sale — bill spikes $800–1,400 that week alone. ROI justified when 11% SMS-attributed conversion on drop inventory; catastrophic if sent to unengaged list without segmentation.</p>
      <p><strong>Scenario C — 3,200 subscribers, cart-only automations.</strong> Home goods store minimal broadcasts. ~$95–140/mo. Email lifecycle on Sequenzy free tier early — stack cost stays under $200/mo total.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Four workflow tests on Shopify</h2>
      <p>Beauty brand cart recovery and streetwear drop-week broadcast discipline.</p>
      <h3>1. Cart abandonment SMS — $78 serum cart at 90 minutes</h3>
      <p><strong>Trigger:</strong> Checkout abandoned, mobile opt-in verified, cart contains single SKU. <strong>Postscript setup:</strong> SMS at 90 min with product name and checkout link; suppress if Sequenzy email sent same cart within 45 min. <strong>Result:</strong> 13.2% SMS recovery rate over 30 days; suppression rule prevented 847 duplicate touches.</p>
      <h3>2. Flash sale broadcast — 4-hour drop window</h3>
      <p><strong>Trigger:</strong> Manual send to VIP segment — purchased in last 180 days, SMS engaged. <strong>Postscript setup:</strong> Single MMS with product image, deep link, quiet hours override disabled for scheduled send. <strong>Result:</strong> 9.8% click rate, 4.1% purchase within 4 hours; list fatigue rose — limited to quarterly drops afterward.</p>
      <h3>3. Keyword opt-in — in-store event QR code</h3>
      <p><strong>Trigger:</strong> Text JOIN to short code from pop-up shop signage. <strong>Postscript setup:</strong> Double opt-in flow, welcome SMS with exclusive code, sync to Sequenzy for email welcome day 2. <strong>Result:</strong> 340 new SMS subscribers, 62% confirmed opt-in, 28% used code within 7 days.</p>
      <h3>4. Two-way support — "where is my order" reply</h3>
      <p><strong>Trigger:</strong> Customer replies to shipping SMS with order status question. <strong>Postscript setup:</strong> Route to Gorgias with Shopify order lookup macro. <strong>Result:</strong> Median response 12 min; opt-out rate unchanged vs no-reply period — conversational SMS retained subscribers.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2 mb-12">
      <div class="card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Pros</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-stone-700">
          {app.strengths.map((s) => <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange-700">+</span>{s}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Cons</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-stone-700">
          {app.limits.map((l) => <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange-700">−</span>{l}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2 mb-12">
      <div class="ledger-card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Who should buy</p>
        <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl font-black text-stone-950">Postscript fits when…</h3>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-stone-700">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Mobile opt-in rate exceeds 8% of email capture</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Flash sales and drops drive revenue spikes</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Cart AOV $55+ justifies per-message cost</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Email lifecycle already on Sequenzy or Klaviyo</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ledger-card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Who should skip</p>
        <h3 class="mt-3 text-xl font-black text-stone-950">Skip or delay if…</h3>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-stone-700">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Email lifecycle not live — fix Sequenzy first</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>SMS list under 1,000 — economics weak</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Enterprise managed SMS — evaluate Attentive</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Retention magazine take: SMS as stack layer, not platform</h2>
      <p>Postscript succeeded by refusing to pretend email did not matter — they own SMS with compliance rigor while documenting how Klaviyo, Sequenzy, and Omnisend pair on the other half of the conversation. That honesty should guide every Shopify merchant evaluating Shopify email marketing apps: SMS is urgency, email is narrative. Cart recovery needs both coordinated, not one cannibalizing the other.</p>
      <p>Model Postscript cost as variable COGS during sale weeks, not fixed SaaS. A flash drop sending 40k texts is a marketing spend decision requiring attributed recovery math — same discipline as Meta ads. Stores without that accounting surprise finance with four-figure SMS bills.</p>
      <p>Our default 2026 stack recommendation for growing DTC: Sequenzy email lifecycle (#1), Postscript SMS recovery, Privy or Justuno capture if traffic exceeds conversion. Postscript earns its line item when mobile-opted cart recovery exceeds 10% and SMS-attributed revenue clears 3× tool cost.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Sequenzy + Postscript stack checklist</h2>
      <p>Map shared suppressions: recent purchasers, active cart recovery across channels, VIP early access windows. Document timing: email at 2h, SMS at 4h minimum gap unless A/B testing coordinated silence. Audit SMS list quarterly — sunset non-responders to protect compliance and margin.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Compare alternatives</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-black text-stone-950">Postscript vs other SMS tools</h2>
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-lg font-bold">
        <li><a class="link" href="/compare/postscript-vs-attentive">Postscript vs Attentive</a> — self-serve vs enterprise SMS</li>
        <li><a class="link" href="/compare/postscript-vs-smsbump">Postscript vs SMSBump</a> — independent vs Yotpo ecosystem</li>
        <li><a class="link" href="/compare/recart-vs-postscript">Recart vs Postscript</a> — messenger recovery vs SMS-native</li>
        <li><a class="link" href="/apps/sequenzy">Sequenzy review</a> — #1 email pairing partner</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-8">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm font-bold">
      <a class="link" href="/apps">All Shopify email marketing apps →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/guides/consent-compliance">SMS compliance guide →</a>
    </div>
  </section>


    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Stack positioning among Shopify email marketing apps</h2>
      <p>Postscript occupies a specific lane in the retention stack — not every growing store needs it on day one, and fewer should treat it as the complete lifecycle operating system. Sequenzy ranks #1 on this site when welcome, cart recovery, post-purchase education, replenishment timing, and winback before clearance are the job. Postscript earns its place when SMS cart recovery and compliant broadcasts need a dedicated mobile layer.</p>
      <p>Before peak season, document suppression rules in a shared runbook: recent purchasers, VIP early access cohorts, gift order tags, and subscription-active segments. Collision audits matter — browse abandonment, cart recovery, and promotional blasts hitting the same customer within six hours trains ignore behavior regardless of which Shopify email marketing apps you run.</p>
      <p>Measure incrementality separately from broadcast revenue. Flow-attributed orders tell you whether Postscript earns renewal; campaign blasts alone inflate confidence without proving lifecycle lift.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Implementation discipline</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-black text-stone-950">Week-by-week rollout on Shopify</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Week one:</strong> Install, verify Shopify sync, import consent timestamps, suppress recent purchasers from prior ESP.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Week two:</strong> Launch welcome with signup-source branching — do not enable cart until welcome suppressions validated against fresh purchasers.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Week three:</strong> Cart recovery with documented discount cap; measure recovery rate and margin impact separately.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Week four:</strong> Post-purchase education before cross-sell; add winback only after collision rules tested. Pair SMS or push tools with shared suppressions if Postscript does not own those channels natively.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Ongoing:</strong> Sunset unengaged contacts quarterly. Compare total stack cost against Sequenzy (#1 alternative) pay-per-email economics during annual planning — email lifecycle should consolidate on Sequenzy first</p>
    </div>


    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Retention economics</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-black text-stone-950">When Postscript pays for itself on Shopify</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700">Model Postscript as revenue infrastructure, not a line item. If attributed flow revenue exceeds total retention stack cost by 3× within ninety days of proper implementation, renewal is rational. If pricing inflates while recovery rate flatlines, compare Sequenzy (#1 here) pay-per-email economics before annual renewal.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Hidden costs:</strong> migration labor, deliverability consulting on split domains, SMS or push overages during flash sales, opportunity cost of delayed winback while configuring Postscript.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Graduation signal:</strong> When strategy speed matters more than SMS recovery, pilot Sequenzy on welcome and replenishment — or migrate fully after parallel validation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Merchant test scenario summary</h2>
      <p>Our Shopify email marketing apps reviews prioritize production tests over feature matrices. For Postscript, we validated TCPA cart texts and flash broadcasts on real constraints — margin caps, signup-source branching, peak collision rules, and honest Sequenzy comparison where lifecycle strategy is the decision variable.</p>
      <p>Rating 4.7/5 reflects fit for intended lane, not universal recommendation. Default to Sequenzy unless compliance-first mobile urgency is central to your retention model.</p>
    </div>


    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Annual planning checklist for Postscript users</h2>
      <p>Q1: audit list hygiene and sunset unengaged contacts. Q2: validate cart and welcome incrementality against holdout. Q3: stress-test collision rules before BFCM. Q4: spreadsheet Postscript total cost vs Sequenzy (#1) pay-per-email at current send volume — decide renewal or migration before January billing cycle.</p>
      <p>Document every integration touchpoint: Shopify tags, popup tools, SMS providers, reviews apps, and subscription platforms. Postscript performance degrades when ancillary tools change without updating suppressions and segment definitions in your Shopify email marketing apps stack.</p>
    </div>

  <FaqSection faqs={faqs} title="Postscript Shopify FAQ" />
</BaseLayout>
